{
  "stem": "3085.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were a number of incidents that, as a child, I'll never forget.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Things like when somebody would be caught in the electrified fence and get killed, and actually burn to death.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, you can't forget those scenes.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You see them touching the wire, and some of them probably doing it because they wanted to commit suicide.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Other may-- others may have done it because they wanted to reach something near the fence, and they were actually drawn to the-- the current was like 10,000 volts, I think.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was a pretty-- pretty powerful electrified fence.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there were other things, where people were punished and beaten by the SS.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I mean, those are things you don't forget.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We had the-- the camp next to us was the gypsy camp.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There were, I think, something like 10 to 20,000 gypsies, mostly children and women.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they were one night just taken away, all of them, to be gassed.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And you could hear their screaming.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "That's the kind of thing you don't forget, and-- and things like that.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Now, towards the end, when the Russians were getting close to the camp, the Germans panicked.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And at that point, I don't even know if Mengele was still there or not.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But at that point, we were recruited to do some work.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "What happened was the-- there was a camp on the other side.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "One side was the gypsy camp, and the other side of us was a camp called Canada, of all things.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I don't know if you ever heard that name [LAUGHS] in connection with Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And Canada was the camp-- God only knows why they named it Canada-- but that was the camp where all the belongings were taken to by-- I mean the belongings of the deportees.",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
